Sentencas: New cobalt-free composites consisting of Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-delta (BSFN) and Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) were investigated as possible cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: BSFN, which was synthesized by auto ignition process, was chemically compatible with SDC up to 1100 degrees C as indicated by X-ray diffraction analysis.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of BSFN reached the maximum value of 57 S.cm(-1) at 450 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value of BSFN was 30.9x10(-6) K-1, much higher than that of typical electrolytes.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior of the composites was analyzed via electrochemical impedance spectroscopy with symmetrical cells BSFN-SDC/SDC/BSFN-SDC.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The area specific interfacial polarization resistance (ASR) decreased with increasing SDC content of the composite.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The area specific interfacial polarization resistance (ASR) at 700 degrees C is only 0.49, 0.34 and 0.31 Omega.cm(2) when 30, 40, and 50 wt% SDC was cooperated to BSFN, respectively.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: These results suggest that BSFN-SDC is a possible candidate for IT-SOFC cathode.
Titulo: Cobalt-free Composite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Ni0.1O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ as Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
